### Attribute-Based Product Filtering Examples
### This file demonstrates how to filter products by attributes

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@authToken = YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN_HERE

### =============================================================================
### Example 1: Filter by Single Attribute
### Returns all products that have attribute with ID 1
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?attributeIds=1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### =============================================================================
### Example 2: Filter by Multiple Attributes (OR Logic)
### Returns products that have ANY of the specified attributes (1, 2, or 3)
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?attributeIds=1,2,3
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### =============================================================================
### Example 3: Combine Attribute Filter with Status
### Returns complete products that have attribute 1 or 2
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?attributeIds=1,2&status=complete
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### =============================================================================
### Example 4: Combine Attribute Filter with Family
### Returns products from family 5 that have attribute 1, 2, or 3
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?attributeIds=1,2,3&familyId=5
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### =============================================================================
### Example 5: Combine Attribute Filter with Category
### Returns products in category 2 that have attribute 1
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?attributeIds=1&categoryId=2
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### =============================================================================
### Example 6: Attribute Filter with Pagination
### Returns first page (10 products) that have attribute 1, 2, or 3
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?attributeIds=1,2,3&page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### =============================================================================
### Example 7: Attribute Filter with Search
### Returns products matching "shirt" that have attribute 1 or 2
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?attributeIds=1,2&search=shirt
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### =============================================================================
### Example 8: Attribute Filter with Sorting
### Returns products with attribute 1, sorted by name ascending
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?attributeIds=1&sortBy=name&sortOrder=asc
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### =============================================================================
### Example 9: Complex Combined Filter
### Returns incomplete products from family 3 with attributes 5 or 6, sorted by date
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?attributeIds=5,6&familyId=3&status=incomplete&sortBy=createdAt&sortOrder=desc
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### =============================================================================
### Example 10: Multiple Filters with Pagination
### Returns page 2 of products with attributes 1,2,3 in category 5, limit 20 per page
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?attributeIds=1,2,3&categoryId=5&page=2&limit=20
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### =============================================================================
### Example 11: Get All Attributes (to know which IDs to use)
### First, fetch all attributes to see their IDs
GET {{baseUrl}}/attributes
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### =============================================================================
### Example 12: Get Single Product to See Its Attributes
### View a specific product to see which attributes it has
GET {{baseUrl}}/products/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### =============================================================================
### Example 13: No Attribute Filter (All Products)
### Returns all products without attribute filtering
GET {{baseUrl}}/products
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### =============================================================================
### How It Works:
###
### 1. The attributeIds parameter accepts a comma-separated list of attribute IDs
### 2. Products are returned if they have ANY of the specified attributes (OR logic)
### 3. This works with both custom attributes and family attributes
### 4. The filter can be combined with other filters for precise results
###
